The Governor of Ebonyi State, Engr. David Umahi has condemned the bandit attack on the Saint Francis Catholic Church in Owo, Ondo State which claimed many lives on Sunday. A statement by Umahi’s Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Hon Francis Nwaze, said Umahi described the incident as “sacrilegious and wondered why people take delight in unnecessary blood letting”. He expressed condolence to the affected families, the Catholic Community, and the Government of Ondo State for the “unfortunate loss of lives”. -Advertisement- Umahi who is also the Chairman of the South East Governor’s Forum called on Security Agencies to rise to the occasion to apprehend the bandits and forestall their reoccurrence in any part of the Country. The Presidential hopeful also prayed to God to grant the deceased rest in His bosom and for the hoodlums to meet their waterloo.